YouTube Watch History Analysis

Exploring My Youtube Watch History

An exploration of my YouTube viewing habits what I watch, how long I watch, and how I feel about the content.

What kind of content do I watch most?

Across all my logged sessions, I found that some categories consistently have longer average video lengths than others.

Bar plot of average video length by category

Vlog or Entertainment categories tend to be longer, while movie and food videos are often short and snappy.
This gives a sense of which content I tend to invest more time into.

Did I actually enjoy what I watched?

Not every video is a hit. I compared enjoyment ratings across whether I would recommend the video or not.

Boxplot showing enjoyment ratings grouped by recommendation

It is not suprising, the videos I would recommend had higher enjoyment ratings. Interestingly, even videos rated maybe still had decent enjoyment scores showing some content sits in a grey zone of okay but not quite recommendable.

How often and how long did I log my data?

Looking at the time gaps between logs, I visualised the minutes between each entry.

Line plot showing minutes between logged entries (last 20 only)

Some entries were logged very close together, while others had big gaps maybe reflecting how I dedicated to give a comment about the video. This plot focuses on the last 20 entries to highlight recent behaviour.

In Conclusion

I learned more about my YouTube habits not just what I watch, but how often I engage, how long Im willing to spend, and what I enjoy most.

Its surprising how much you can reflect on personal behaviour just from a spreadsheet and a few plots!
